data.title: Hollyoaks Specials
data.meta_description: The daily soap that follows the loves, lives and misdemeanours of a group of people living in the Chester village of Hollyoaks where anything could, and frequently does, happen...
data.text:
A video spin-off from 1998 which sees Rob Hawthorne seek revenge against Kurt Benson. The storyline comes to a dramatic conclusion with Rob and Kurt fighting on a boat. Rob rushes at Kurt, however he moves out of the way and Rob falls into the sea, with everyone believing he is dead.

A drama-documentary looking back at the past 14 years, showing classic clips from the series. Ste Hay and Cheryl Brady go to a cinema where old clips from Hollyoaks are being shown by a familiar face. It was presented by Bernard Latham who played Gordon Cunningham. For the episode, special sequences were filmed between old clips of the show. They parodied such films as Stanley Kubrick's The Shining and Randal Kleiser's Grease.

One-off special following the Savage family's black sheep Dennis as he heads to Liverpool with Leanne, Barney and Scott in search of a headline act for Will's fundraising party. He and his allies are forced to put aside their differences to track down an artist impressive enough to satisfy his cousin's disgruntled guests .

A look back at the early years of Hollyoaks. It's Christmas Day 1997, and Cindy goes into labour alone. Jambo plans his future with Dawn, but he doesn't realise how unwell she really is.

Sarah, Ali and Jodi take you through three sections to the complete overall body exercise regime: the warm up, the dance workout and the cool down. This cardiovascular workout will help you to tone and condition your body in an easy and fun way. Learn how to work every muscle in this simple dance routine as well as how to relax and revitalise your body.

Two of Chester's finest acting talents, Matt Milburn and Roxanne McKee, flee the Hollyoaks nest to embark upon an awesome adventure Down Under. As soon as Matt and Roxy, aka Joe and Louise, arrive in Sydney, they begin their whirlwind tour of Extreme Australia. From swimming with sharks to skydiving, Matt and Roxy compete for an uber-deluxe, super-plush luxury holiday in Oz. But can they handle the Hollyoaks Extreme Challenge?

A classic episode from 1997. How will Tony react when Julie has a change of heart on their wedding day? Meanwhile, Jude is trapped when she sets fire to her flat.

A chance to watch the first ever episode from 1995. Bad boy Kurt's been chasing Natasha for weeks. Will he finally make an impression when he comes to the rescue of Natasha and her pals?

Hosted by Chris Fountain (Justin Burton) and Carley Stenson (Steph Dean), this special was commissioned by BBC America to bring USA viewers up-to-speed on who's who and what's what, ahead of airing episodes from late 2006, in the run up to The Dog fire.

"If I hadnt seen that episode that day, I wouldnt be here now talking to you."

John Junior was planning to end their life until they saw Darren and Nancys reaction to Kyles death. True Stories looks at the fictional storylines in Hollyoaks and how theyve made life-changing impacts on real peoples lives.

Justin Beck grew up believing that loving another man was sinful. After a long and difficult journey, hes now confident to say "I love the fact that Im gay."

Justin opens up to Ross Adams (Scott Drinkwell) about his own experience of gay conversion therapy and the steps he took to recover from the trauma.

Anorexia always controlled me in the past. Whereas I control anorexia now. Ben Robinson shares with Nadine Mulkerrin (Cleo McQueen) his experience of having an eating disorder, a storyline also portrayed by Nadines character in Hollyoaks.

As Spring arrives in Hollyoaks, get up to speed on the top stories! Sienna and Ste do the dirty work for new boy Ethan, Warren's past catches up with him, and 'Love Shaq' has a lot of making up to do.

"Why Should I carry my keys between my fingers?" In an upcoming storyline, #Hollyoaks will be tackling the issue of radicalised misogyny. The #WhyShouldI campaign is here to tackle the spectrum of misogyny and challenge why women feel they need to change their behaviour, when men are often not conscious of theirs.

How have you found my childhood address?!

In a world where we share so much information about ourselves online and on social media, do we really know the risks?

We asked a professional hacker to find private information about Hollyoaks cast members Haiesha Mistry, Owen Warner, Niamh Blackshaw and Billy Price using just their names and email addresses.

Everything the hacker found was publicly available on social media and search engines, and the results were pretty shocking!

The popular Channel 4 soap opera, following the fortunes of a host of young characters in Chester, receives its video premiere here with the concluding episode to a storyline built up over four nights on television. If you tuned in between 12-15 October to follow the plot on C4, find out the outcome with this tape, released the following day, and not to be shown on terrestrial TV.

Sex, lies and betrayal. That's the reality for Geri, Luke and Ben over a weekend they'll never forget! Hollyoaks: Indecent Behaviour is the no-holds barred feature length special that tells the truth behind the rumours and answers the questions on everyone's lips about 48 hours that changed everything. When Geri arrives at the airport to meet her football star fianc, Jason Cunliffe, she spots a mysterious blonde, Alyson, with Jason's manager, Dion. What games has Jason been playing? Has he been scoring both on and off the field? At a wild, all-night party, dubious tackles abound as Beth Morgan and footballer Scott Anderson are drawn into the revelries. Meanwhile, what happened to Luke to push him back over the edge? It's all revealed in this steamy, sexy and hard hitting Hollyoaks special, available exclusively on video for a limited period.

Breda shows how monstrous she really is, while Goldie is growing suspicious of her mum. Verity has to make a decision about her future, and could Tony steal a chance at freedom?

Winter has arrived in Hollyoaks! But before you dive into the final juicy season of 2022, Maxine and Scott spill the tea on all the dangerous and difficult goings-on in the village...

This is an immersive experience of Maxines walk home after a night out. This may be a walk, but take a seat, wear headphones to hear her thoughts and allow her to take you on her journey, to know the feeling.

In this episode of Hollyoaks IRL, entrepreneur, Dominic McGregor meets James Sutton (John Paul McQueen) and they discuss the daily struggles of an alcohol addiction and thoughts of suicide. They talk about the effects addiction can have on family members and friends, and we also hear how Dominic managed to overcome his dependance on alcohol and turn his life around.
